# LaTeX Paper Formatting — Follow docs/latex_exmaple.tex

When generating LaTeX tables or paper content, always follow the patterns in `docs/latex_exmaple.tex`.

## Table Rules

**Wide metric tables** (many numeric columns — baseline/mitigation results):
- Use `table*[!t]` (full-width, top of page)
- Column spec: `@{}lrrrrrrrrr@{}` — left-aligned model name, right-aligned numbers, `@{}` removes outer padding
- Use `\footnotesize` inside the table
- Booktabs only: `\toprule`, `\midrule`, `\bottomrule` — never `\hline`
- Add threshold footnotes with `\multicolumn{N}{l}{\scriptsize Thresholds: ...}` between `\bottomrule` and `\end{tabular}`

```latex
\begin{table*}[!t]
\centering
\caption{Baseline Fairness Metrics}
\label{tab:baseline}
\footnotesize
\begin{tabular}{@{}lrrrrrrrrr@{}}
\toprule
Model & Acc & F1 & AUC & FPR & DPD & EOD & DI & SPD Viol & EOD Viol \\
\midrule
Logistic Regression & 0.9771 & 0.1213 & ... \\
\bottomrule
\multicolumn{10}{l}{\scriptsize Thresholds: EU AI Act $|\mathrm{SPD}| \leq 0.1$, $|\mathrm{EOD}| \leq 0.05$, $\mathrm{DI} \geq 0.8$.}
\end{tabular}
\end{table*}
```

**Narrow tables** (2-3 text columns — model configs, audit checks):
- Use `table[htbp]` (single-column)
- Column spec: `@{}p{width} p{width}@{}` with explicit widths
- Use `\footnotesize`

```latex
\begin{table}[htbp]
\centering
\caption{Model configurations.}
\label{tab:models}
\footnotesize
\begin{tabular}{@{}p{3.5cm} p{4.5cm}@{}}
\toprule
Model & Configuration \\
\midrule
...
\bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\end{table}
```

## Placement — Never Use [H]

- Do NOT use `[H]` placement or `\usepackage{float}`.
- Use `[!t]` for wide `table*`/`figure*`, `[htbp]` for single-column `table`/`figure`.

## Reference Document Quotes

Use `\begin{quote}\textit{...}\end{quote}` for excerpts from reference PDFs.
